content.problemStatement:
The `clear()` method is a member function used to remove all characters from a string, making it an empty string. It is useful when reusing the same string variable without retaining old content.

**Syntax:**
```cpp
string_variable.clear();
```

---

 **Example:**
```cpp
#include 
using namespace std;

int main() {
    string message = "Temporary text";  // Initialize string with content

    message.clear();  // Remove all characters

    cout << "Message: " << message << endl; 

    return 0;
}
```
**Expected Output:**
```default
Message:
```

